 A Pain and Gain report released by CoreLogic for the December quarter has revealed that home resales recording a gross loss were at an all time low with more properties making a decent profit .
When compared to their purchase price , only 8.6 percent of homes had recorded a loss and 32.3 percent had shown properties selling for more than double their original price .
